        <presentation>
          <material>
            <mattext texttype="text/html">&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Animated transitions provide an eye pleasing effect when updating visual elements. For the user it is easier to follow data changes. (select all that apply)&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</mattext>
          </material>
          <response_lid ident="response1" rcardinality="Multiple">
            <render_choice>
              <response_label ident="56894">
                <material>
                  <mattext texttype="text/plain">You have to add the "transition()" operator to apply transitions to the current selection</mattext>
                </material>
              </response_label>
              <response_label ident="19469">
                <material>
                  <mattext texttype="text/plain">By default the transition you specified will start automatically when the code is getting executed</mattext>
                </material>
              </response_label>
              <response_label ident="21995">
                <material>
                  <mattext texttype="text/plain">By using the keywords "delay()" and "duration()" you can specify individual settings for the transition</mattext>
                </material>
              </response_label>
              <response_label ident="68340">
                <material>
                  <mattext texttype="text/plain">To achieve object constancy when data items enter and exit (track a particular data point visually during the transition) with d3 you have to specify a key function as the second argument to selection.data</mattext>
                </material>
              </response_label>
            </render_choice>
          </response_lid>
        </presentation>
